   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" xml:lang="grc" subtype="transcription" xml:id="zoor0312.transcription" corresp="#zoor0312.translation">
            <p>
               <g type="cross">+</g>
               <choice>
                  <sic>Ἷς</sic>
                  <corr>Εἷς</corr>
               </choice> Θεός, ὁ πἀντων Δεσ<lb break="no"/>πότης. <choice>
                  <sic>Μνημεῖαν</sic>
                  <corr>Μνημεῖον</corr>
               </choice> Κύρας<lb/> Κασσισέου, <choice>
                  <sic>ἀποθανοῦσ<unclear>α</unclear>
                  </sic>
                  <corr>ἀποθανόθσης</corr>
               </choice>
               <lb/> μετὰ καλοῦ <choice>
                  <sic>ἀνῶματος</sic>
                  <corr>ὀνόματος</corr>
               </choice>
               <lb/> καὶ κ<unclear>αλῆς</unclear> πίστεως ἐτῶ<lb/>
               <supplied reason="lost">ν</supplied>
               <gap reason="illegible" atLeast="17" atMost="18" unit="character"/>
               <lb/>
               <gap reason="illegible" atLeast="12" atMost="13" unit="character"/>
               <supplied reason="lost">
                  <unclear>Ξ</unclear>ανθι</supplied>
               <lb break="no"/>κοῦ δευτέρᾳ <expan>
                  <abbr>ἠμ</abbr>
                  <ex>έρᾳ</ex>
               </expan> Κυρίου <lb/>
               <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="zoor0312.translation" corresp="#zoor0312.transcription">
            <p> One (is) the God, the Lord of all. Monument of Kyra (daughter) of Kassisseos,
                    who died having a good name and good faith (at the age) of...on the second (day)
                    of [the month Xan]thikos, on the ...day of the...Lord..</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription provides a day and a month, the 2nd of Xanthikos (March 23), but not
               a year. Still, the inscription has been dated on the strength of other factors to the
               second half of the 5th century CE. The author notes that the names which appear
               in this inscription are also found elsewhere at Ghor es-Safi.</p>
         </div>
